<subSubSection pageId="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1289,1710]" pageId="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,1505,1530]" pageId="13">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
The specimen captured in Fuenteventura coincides in the coloration as well as in the arrangement of the tentacles and the eyes with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bahia &amp; Schroedl" authorityYear="2016" box="[673,764,1542,1565]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="13" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="wirtzi">
<emphasis box="[673,764,1542,1565]" italics="true" pageId="13">P. wirtzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by Bahia &amp; Schrödl 2015, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1335,1541,1566]" name="Senegal" pageId="13">Senegal</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bahia &amp; Schroedl" authorityYear="2016" box="[1345,1436,1542,1565]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="13" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="wirtzi">
<emphasis box="[1345,1436,1542,1565]" italics="true" pageId="13">P. wirtzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the presence of two male copulatory organs and a conspicuous unique pigmentation pattern of multiple yellow and white fine lines across a dark (brown to black) background colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1289,1710]" pageId="13">
Due to its characteristic colour and drawing pattern, we deduce that the specimens identified by Vera et al 2009 as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lang" authorityYear="1884" box="[181,364,1685,1710]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="13" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Pseudocerotidae</taxonomicName>
sp. 4 is 
<emphasis box="[457,699,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="13">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bahia &amp; Schroedl" authorityYear="2016" box="[457,696,1685,1710]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="13" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="wirtzi">Pseudobiceros wirtzi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
